Amazon Supply Chain Intelligence — Full Stack Delivery Risk Platform

This submission-ready project predicts delivery delay risk levels:
- 0 = On-Time
- 1 = At Risk
- 2 = Delayed

Tech Stack
- Frontend: Vite + React + JavaScript
- Backend: FastAPI + Python
- Model: RandomForest (loaded from final_model.pkl)
- Storage: SQLite for prediction history

Project Structure
- backend/app/main.py → FastAPI endpoints
- backend/app/preprocessing.py → raw input to engineered feature vector
- backend/app/predictor.py → model loading and inference
- backend/app/database.py → history persistence
- backend/app/generate_metrics.py → comparative model evaluation generator
- frontend/src/pages/DashboardPage.jsx → integrated UI for predict/batch/metrics/history

Features
- Login with JWT token
- Single prediction API + UI form
- Batch CSV prediction API + UI upload
- Model metrics dashboard (from model_metrics.json)
- Prediction history table

Backend Setup (Windows PowerShell)
1) Open terminal in Amazon-Delivery-ML folder
2) Create and activate virtual environment:
	python -m venv .venv
	.\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
3) Install dependencies:
	pip install -r backend/requirements.txt
4) (Optional) set env vars from backend/.env.example
5) Start backend:
	uvicorn backend.app.main:app --reload --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8000

Frontend Setup
1) Open second terminal in Amazon-Delivery-ML/frontend
2) Install dependencies:
	npm install
3) (Optional) set API base URL:
	set VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8000/api
4) Start frontend:
	npm run dev

Default Demo Login
- username: admin
- password: admin123

Metrics Generation (Comparative Evaluation)
To regenerate model comparison metrics from feature_data.csv:
- python -m backend.app.generate_metrics

API Endpoints
- GET /api/health
- POST /api/auth/login
- POST /api/predict
- POST /api/predict/batch
- GET /api/metrics
- GET /api/history

Batch CSV Template
- Use backend/sample_batch_input.csv as template for upload.

Notes
- Ensure final_model.pkl exists at project root (already present).
- For submission, replace default credentials and JWT secret in production.

